Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 20
Edition:
Quote: come down: a river is said to come down when it floods. Though locals rarely even notice the apparent phenomenon, visitors to Canterbury and Otago are often surprised to see that the rivers fed by the Southern Alps have come down in pleasantly warm weather; this is due to thawing rains on the Main Divide.
